    "comment": "Rationale: * GFP-Triad3A colocalized with clathrin-DsRed in dendritic shafts and spines of hippocam- pal neurons (Figure 6A) but not with the postsynaptic density marker Homer-DsRed (Figure 6B).\n* Endogenous Triad3A in dendritic spines tightly overlapped with clathrin- DsRed within a subdomain of the spine (Figure 6C)\n* Immunogold electron microscopy (EM) of rat CA1 hippocampus in vivo shows Triad3A immunogold labeling near the membrane and on vesicle-like structures in both presynaptic terminals and postsynaptic spines (Figure 6E).\n* (>30%) of gold particles were positioned along the plasma membrane near the PSD. Experimental description: Supp info: Hippocampal neurons were isolated from E18 rat embryos and cultured as previously described (Ehlers, 2000)",
